.\" mew.1 — manual page for mew
.\" -----------------------------------------------------------------------
.TH MEW 1 "March 23, 2026" "mew 0.3.0" "User Commands"
.\" -----------------------------------------------------------------------
.SH NAME
mew \- preprocess study notes and synthesize speech via Kokoro TTS
.\" -----------------------------------------------------------------------
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mew
.RB [ \-h ]
.RB [ \-i " | " \-p ]
.RB [ \-n ]
.RB [ \-P ]
.RB [ \-v
.IR voice ]
.RB [ \-m
.IR model ]
.RB [ \-s
.IR speed ]
.I file
.RI [ file\~ .\|.\|.]
.\" -----------------------------------------------------------------------
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B mew
takes one or more note files, runs each through a text preprocessing
pipeline optimised for natural-sounding speech output, then synthesizes
the result to a WAV file using the Kokoro TTS engine (ONNX) via a
self-contained Python venv.
.PP
By default, only the synthesized audio is written:
.TP
.I file.mew.wav
The synthesized audio, ready for playback.
.PP
The intermediate preprocessed text is used internally but not saved
unless
.B \-i
is given.
.\" -----------------------------------------------------------------------
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print a short usage summary and exit.
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Print the version number and exit.
.TP
.BR \-i ", " \-\-intermediate
Intermediate only: preprocess the input and write
.IR file.mew.md ,
then exit without synthesizing.
Mutually exclusive with
.BR \-p .
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-preprocessed
Pre-processed: treat
.I file
as already preprocessed and skip straight to synthesis.
Mutually exclusive with
.BR \-i .
.TP
.BR \-n ", " \-\-dry\-run
Preview preprocessed text on stdout and an estimated synthesis time on
stderr; do not create any files.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-voice " " \fIVOICE\fR
One-off voice override for this invocation (does not change config).
See
.B CONFIGURATION
for available voices.
.TP
.BR \-m ", " \-\-model " " \fIMODEL\fR
One-off model override for this invocation (does not change config).
Must be a downloaded model.
.TP
.BR \-P ", " \-\-play
Auto-play audio after synthesis.
Mutually exclusive with
.BR \-i .
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-speed " " \fISPEED\fR
Playback speed multiplier, 1.0\(en3.0 (default: 1.0).
Speeds up to 2.0 are handled natively by Kokoro (preserving prosody);
speeds above 2.0 additionally apply WSOLA time-stretching.
.\" -----------------------------------------------------------------------
.SH CONFIGURATION
Run
.B mew config
to interactively select the TTS model and voice.
Preferences are saved to
.I ~/.config/mew/prefs.json
and used on every subsequent synthesis run.
.PP
.B Subcommands:
.TP
.B mew config
Interactive prompt: offers to change model, voice, playback method, and speed.
.TP
.B mew config model
Change model only.
Available models (Kokoro-82M v1.0 ONNX variants):
.BR int8 " (compact, 88 MB),"
.BR fp16 " (balanced, 169 MB),"
.BR fp32 " (full precision, 310 MB)."
If the chosen model has not been downloaded, you are prompted to download it.
.TP
.B mew config voice
Change voice only.
American female voices:
.BR Heart ", " Bella ", " Sarah ", " Nova ", " Nicole ", " Jessica .
American male voices:
.BR Adam ", " Michael ", " Eric ", " Liam .
British female voices:
.BR Emma ", " Alice .
British male voices:
.BR George ", " Daniel .
.TP
.B mew config playback
Change the playback method (terminal or app).
.TP
.B mew config speed
Change the default speed multiplier.
.TP
.B mew config delete
Interactively select a downloaded model to remove from the cache.
Only downloaded models are listed.
If the selected model is the active model, a warning is shown before
confirming deletion.
.TP
.B mew config show
Print current model and voice settings without making changes.
.\" -----------------------------------------------------------------------
.SH PREPROCESSING PIPELINE
The following transformations are applied to the input, in order:
.TP
.B Deduplication
Repeated sections (identified by duplicate
.B ##
headings) are removed; only the first occurrence is kept.
.TP
.B Unicode normalisation
Typographic characters are replaced with ASCII equivalents:
curly quotes become straight quotes, em\-dashes become
.B \-\-
(a dramatic pause marker), en\-dashes become
.IR " to " ,
and the Unicode ellipsis character becomes
.BR ... .
.TP
.B Bracket removal
Citation markers such as
.B [1]
or
.B [1,2]
are stripped entirely.
Bracket\-enclosed text such as
.B [word]
has its brackets removed but the content kept.
.TP
.B Parenthetical expansion
Common parenthetical abbreviations are rewritten as inline clauses:
.RS
.PD 0
.TP 16
.BI (ex. " X" )
\(-> , such as \fIX\fR,
.TP
.BI (i.e. " X" )
\(-> , that is \fIX\fR,
.TP
.BI (e.g. " X" )
\(-> , for example \fIX\fR,
.PD
.RE
.TP
.B Numeric range expansion
Patterns such as
.B 10\-20
are expanded to
.IR "ten to twenty" .
Year ranges such as
.B 1990\-2024
become
.IR "nineteen ninety to twenty twenty\-four" .
Exact millennium years use the thousand form:
.B 2000
becomes
.IR "two thousand" .
.TP
.B Slash handling
.B and/or
becomes
.IR "and or" ;
other
.IB word / word
patterns become
.IR "word or word" .
.TP
.B Abbreviation expansion
.RS
.PD 0
.TP 10
.B e.g.
\(-> for example
.TP
.B i.e.
\(-> that is
.TP
.B ex.
\(-> for example
.TP
.B etc.
\(-> and so on
.PD
.RE
.TP
.B Markdown stripping
Heading markers
.RB ( # ", " ## ", " ### \~\[u2026])
and emphasis markers
.RB ( ** ", " * ", " __ ", " _ )
are removed.
.TP
.B Acronym expansion (first use)
Known acronyms are expanded on their first appearance only.
Currently:
.B ACA
\(->
.IR "ACA, the American Counseling Association," .
.TP
.B Introductory\-clause commas
Sentences beginning with a subordinating conjunction or preposition
.RB ( When ", " During ", " Before ", " After ", " Because ", " Although ,
.RI etc. )
that are missing a comma before the main\-clause subject have one
inserted automatically.
.TP
.B Breathing commas
In sentences over 20 words, a comma is inserted before the first
coordinating conjunction
.RB ( and ", " but ", " or ", " so ", " yet )
that does not already have one, provided at least 10 words precede it.
This prevents the flat, breathless quality of long unbroken clauses.
.TP
.B List numbering
Bullet items
.RB ( \- )
following a recognised label line
.RB ( "Potential Problems:" " or " "Recommendations and Resolutions:" )
are replaced with spoken ordinals:
.IR "Number one: \[u2026]" ", " "Number two: \[u2026]" ,
and so on.
Both labels reset the counter independently.
.TP
.B Section break pauses
Each
.B ##
heading is preceded by an ellipsis line and surrounded by double blank
lines, producing a natural silence at each section transition.
Label lines are followed by an extra blank line for additional breathing
room before the numbered items.
.TP
.B Terminal period
Any non\-empty line that still lacks terminal punctuation
.RB ( . ", " ? ", " ! ", " : )
has a period appended, ensuring the engine pauses at every logical break.
.TP
.B Quote wrapping
Content lines are wrapped in double quotes
.RB ( \(lq\~\fItext\fR\~\(rq ).
Kokoro\-family TTS engines read quoted text with more varied intonation
and emphasis, reducing the flat, robotic quality of unquoted input.
Blank lines, section break markers, and lines already containing quotes
are left unwrapped.
.\" -----------------------------------------------------------------------
.SH FILES
.TP
.I $(brew \-\-prefix)/bin/mew
Wrapper script that delegates to the mew entry point inside the Homebrew-managed venv.
.TP
.I /opt/homebrew/var/mew/venv/
Python virtual environment containing mew, kokoro\-onnx, and their
dependencies.
Managed by Homebrew; do not modify directly.
.TP
.I ~/.config/mew/prefs.json
Persistent model and voice preferences.
Created automatically when preferences are first saved via
.BR "mew config" .
.TP
.I ~/.cache/mew/models/
Kokoro model and voice files, downloaded automatically on first use or
via
.BR "mew config" .
Contains the ONNX model file and voice embeddings.
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/mew/synthesis.jsonl
Synthesis timing log.
Each line records the phoneme count, elapsed seconds, and model alias
for one synthesis run.
After at least three entries for a given model, mew displays an estimated
progress bar during synthesis.
.\" -----------------------------------------------------------------------
.SH EXAMPLES
Synthesize a single note file (produces notes.mew.wav):
.PP
.RS
.B mew notes.md
.RE
.PP
Synthesize and auto-play:
.PP
.RS
.B mew \-P notes.md
.RE
.PP
Synthesize at 1.5\(mu speed with a specific voice:
.PP
.RS
.B mew \-s 1.5 \-v Sarah notes.md
.RE
.PP
Export the preprocessed text for inspection, then synthesize it:
.PP
.RS
.nf
mew \-i notes.md        # writes notes.mew.md
less notes.mew.md       # review
mew \-p notes.mew.md    # writes notes.mew.wav
.fi
.RE
.PP
Preview preprocessed text without creating files:
.PP
.RS
.B mew \-n notes.md
.RE
.\" -----------------------------------------------------------------------
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Invalid arguments, missing input file, missing dependency, or synthesis
error.
.\" -----------------------------------------------------------------------
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR python3 (1)
.\" -----------------------------------------------------------------------
.SH BUGS
Introductory\-clause comma insertion uses a heuristic position threshold
and may occasionally miss or misplace a comma in unusual sentence
constructions.
.PP
Acronym expansion is limited to a small built\-in list; acronyms in other
subject domains are not expanded automatically.
.\" -----------------------------------------------------------------------
.SH AUTHOR
Written for personal study\-note workflows.
